{"name": "pyrf96", "metadata": {"name": "pyrf96", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "matplotlib"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733972732}, "documentation": [""], "modules": [{"name": "pyrf96", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pyrf96.InvDataCov", "xref": {"fqname": "pyrf96._pyrf96.InvDataCov", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyrf96.plot_misfit_profile", "xref": {"fqname": "pyrf96._pyrf96.plot_misfit_profile", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyrf96.plot_RFs", "xref": {"fqname": "pyrf96._pyrf96.plot_RFs", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyrf96.plotRFm", "xref": {"fqname": "pyrf96._pyrf96.plotRFm", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyrf96.rfcalc", "xref": {"fqname": "pyrf96._pyrf96.rfcalc", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96", "documentation": ["-----------------------------------------------------------------------", "This script is a c-types interface between Receiver function routines and python", "Most parameters relating to the Receiver Function are set within the Fortran routine.", "Fortran routines for Receiver function calculation by T. Shibutani", "M. Sambridge and Juerg Hauser,", "RSES, Dec., 2024.", "-----------------------------------------------------------------------"], "functions": [{"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96.rfcalc", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sn", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mtype", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fs", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "gauss_a", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "water_c", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "angle", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "time_shift", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ndatar", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "v60", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "seed", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["    Calculate synthetic surface wave dispersion curves for a given earth model, with optional addition of noise added in frequency domain.\n\n    This is a slim Fortran wrapper around RF.F90 from Shibutani et al. (1996), which uses the Thomson-Haskell matrix formulation.\n    Further details may be found.\n\n\n    Args:\n    model (np.ndarray)               : Triplet defining layered model. meaning depends on mytpe, with shape (npts,3).\n    sn (float,optional)              : Signal to noise ratio used to add correlated Gaussian noise to output.\n    mtype (int, optional)            : Indicator for format of velocity model (default=0)\n                                       model(1,i) is Vs velocity of layer i;\n                                       model(2,i) is vpvs ratio of layer i;\n                                       mtype = 0 -> model(0,i) is the depth of Voronoi nuclei defining layer i;\n                                       mtype = 1 -> model(0,i) is the thickness of layer i;\n                                       mtype = 2 -> model(0,i) is depth of lower interface of layer i;\n    fs (float, optional)             : Sampling frequency (default=25 samples/s)\n    gauss_a (float, optional)        : Number 'a' defining the width of the gaussian filter in the deconvolution (default=2.5)\n    water_c (float, optional)        : Water level used in deconvolution (default=0.0001)\n    angle (float, optional)          : Angle in degrees of incoming teleseismic plane wave from vertical (default=35 degrees)\n    time_shift (float, optional)     : Time shift before the first p pusle (default=5s)\n    ndatar (int,optional)            : Number of time time steps of output waveform\n    v60 (float,optional)             : P-wave velocity (km/s) needed to compute the ray parameter from angle (default=8.043 km/s)\n    seed (int,optional)              : Random set for noise gneration\n\nReturns:\n    time (np.array, size ndatar )  : Time series time in seconds.\n    wdata (np.array, size ndatar)  : The Receiver function amplitude."]}, {"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96.v2mod", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vmin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "vmax", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dmin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dmax", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96.InvDataCov", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "width", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "Ar", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ndata", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["#################################################################################"]}, {"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96.InvDataCovSub", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "width", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "Ar", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ndata", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ind", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["#################################################################################"]}, {"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96.plot_misfit_profile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "misfit", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xtrue", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "iparam", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["#################################################################################"]}, {"name": "pyrf96._pyrf96.l2mod", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vmin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "vmax", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dmin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dmax", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["###################################################